USABILITY TESTING FINDINGS REPORT

Summary:
Five participants completed usability testing on the MovieGo prototype.

Key Findings:

1. Search feature lacked visibility.
2. Seat selection indicators were unclear.
3. Payment action button did not stand out.
4. Users wanted more information on the confirmation screen.

Usability Metrics:

Average Satisfaction Score: 3.8/5

Task Completion Rate: 96%

Average Errors per User: 1.4

Recommendations:

* Move search bar to the top of the home screen.
* Add color-coded seat indicators.
* Increase payment button contrast and size.
* Improve booking confirmation details.

Conclusion:

The prototype performs well overall but requires minor usability improvements to enhance user experience and reduce user errors.
